I only copy &amp; pasted the conclusion since the review itself is, granted, way too long to quote in full (and expect people to read it) <br>
<br>
I should once again stress that Isel is known as a hopeless fanboi by most betas, but even her concedes that there are too many things wrong with the game.<br>
<br>
Don't get me wrong, I've been following Horizons' rollercoaster-ride development since late 2000 with high expections. But for the sake of the health of MMORPG gaming industry, please let's -stop- supporting games in alpha-condition...<br>
<br>
I know this will fall on deaf ears and the developers will once again manage to sell thousands half-working games. More power to them and their marketing teams... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=venvenae>Venvenae</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://home.satx.rr.com/perilousendeavor/venEQPA.jpg width=94 height=172" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Heartbreaker</span><br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/8/03 4:25 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2170.topic&index=36>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home.satx.rr.com/perilousendeavor/venEQPA.jpg width=94 height=172></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: re</span><hr size=1> US release is tomorrow... servers up at midnight tonight...<br>
